        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Ghostly food appears on cracked plates as they float above the table. The faint outline of children can occasionally be seen as the ectoplasmic food is flung throughout the room.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[occultism|dc:17] (trained) to weaken the spiritual energy in the room, @Check[acrobatics|dc:18] (trained) to pluck a floating plate out of the air, or @Check[intimidation|dc:19] (trained) to reprimand one of the ghostly children for their poor behavior; each successful check disables one of four plates</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 2
            },
            "publication": {
                "license": "ORC",
                "remaster": true,
                "title": "Pathfinder Adventure Path: Hellbreakers"
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt deactivates 1 minute after all creatures leave the room or after all four plates are destroyed. After 1 hour, if at least one plate remains, the haunt reactivates. If disabled, the haunt resets after 1 day and the plates magically reassemble. The haunt is permanently destroyed when the attic whisperer in area <strong>D5</strong> is destroyed.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(4 actions) For each plate disabled or destroyed, the haunt has 1 fewer action. On each action, spectral food is flung off a plate at a different living creature in the room. This ranged Strike doesn't provoke reactions. A creature critically hit by a flung food Strike is also @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Dazzled] for 1 round.</p>"
        },
